<subsection xml:id="subsec-reflection-of-different-shapes-on-a-plane">
    <title>Reflection of Different Shapes on a Plane</title>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-reflection-on-the-y-axis">
        <title>Reflection on the y-Axis</title>

        <activity>
            <p>
              <term>Work in groups</term>
            </p>
            <p>
              Here is a step by step approach on reflection of a triangle on the line <m>x = 0.</m>
            </p>
             
            <image>
              <latex-image label="object_mirror_line">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                  % Draw the grid lines
                  \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                    % Draw x and y axes
                    \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                    \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
    
                    % Grid and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1); % Tick marks on x-axis
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }
    
                    \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y); % Tick marks on y-axis
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }
      
                  % Draw the original triangle
                  \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[blue,thick] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \node[blue] at (-2,3.1) {A};
                  \node[blue] at (-4.1,0) {B};
                  \node[blue] at (-0.9,-2.1) {C};
      
                  % Draw the mirror line x = 0
                  \draw[red,thick] (0,-4) -- (0,4) node[above right] {$x = 0$};
                \end{tikzpicture}
              </latex-image>
            </image>
      
            <p>
              Draw a perpendicular line from vertex <m>A</m> to the line of reflection <m>x = 0</m> and measure the distance by counting the 
              number of squares between vertex <m>A</m> and the reflection line <m>M.</m> Repeat this process for vertices <m>B \text { and }C.</m>
            </p>
      
            <image>
              <latex-image label="object_mirror_line_perpendicular_distance_1">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                  % Draw the grid lines
                  \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                    % Draw x and y axes
                    \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                    \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
    
                  % Grid and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1); % Tick marks on x-axis
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }
    
                    \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y); % Tick marks on y-axis
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }
      
                  % Draw the original triangle
                  \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[blue,thick] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \node[blue] at (-2,3.1) {A};
                  \node[blue] at (-4.1,0) {B};
                  \node[blue] at (-0.9,-2.1) {C};
      
                  % Draw the mirror line x = 0
                  \draw[red,thick] (0,-4) -- (0,4) node[above right] {$x = 0$};
      
                  %Draw the perpendicular distance to M
                  \draw[black] (-2,3) -- (0,3);
                  \draw[black] (-4,-0) -- (0,0);
                  \draw[black] (-1,-2) -- (0,-2);
      
                  %Draw the the angle at the perpendicular bisector
                  \draw(-.4,3) -- (-.4,3.4) -- (0,3.4);
                  \draw(-.4,0) -- (-.4,.4) -- (0,.4);
                  \draw(-.4,-2) -- (-.4,-1.6) -- (0,-1.6);
                \end{tikzpicture}
              </latex-image>
            </image>
            
            <p>
              Determine the position of the reflected vertices. For vertex <m>A</m> the perpendicular distance between the vertex and the y-axis is 
              <m>2</m> squares. Count <m>2</m> squares from the y-axis to the opposite side and mark that point as <m>A',</m> 
              which is the reflected image of vertex <m>A.</m> Repeat the same procedure the remaining vertices <m>B \text { and }C.</m>
            </p>
      
            <image>
              <latex-image label="object_mirror_line_perpendicular_distance_2">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                  % Draw the grid lines
                  \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                  % Draw x and y axes
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
    
                  % Grid and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1); % Tick marks on x-axis
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }
    
                    \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y); % Tick marks on y-axis
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }
      
                  % Draw the original triangle
                  \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[blue,thick] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \node[blue] at (-2,3.1) {A};
                  \node[blue] at (-4.1,0) {B};
                  \node[blue] at (-0.9,-2.1) {C};
      
                  % Draw the mirror line x = 0
                  \draw[red,thick] (0,-4) -- (0,4) node[above right] {$x = 0$};
      
                  %Draw the perpendicular distance to M
                  \draw[black] (-2,3) -- (2,3) node[green,above right] {$A'$};
                  \draw[black] (-4,-0) -- (4,0) node[green,above right] {$B'$};
                  \draw[black] (-1,-2) -- (1,-2) node[green,above right] {$C'$};
                \end{tikzpicture}
              </latex-image>
            </image>
      
            <p>
              Connect the reflected vertices <m>A',B' \text { and }C'</m> to create the reflected image of the triangle <m>ABC.</m>
            </p>
      
            <image>
              <shortdescription>Reflected triangle</shortdescription>
              <latex-image label="triangle-1ne">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                  
                  % Draw the grid lines
                  \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                  % Draw x and y axes
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
    
                  % Grid and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1); % Tick marks on x-axis
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }
    
                    \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y); % Tick marks on y-axis
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }
      
      
                  % Draw the original triangle
                  \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[blue,thick] (-2,3) -- (-4,0) -- (-1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \node[blue] at (-2,3.1) {A};
                  \node[blue] at (-4.1,0) {B};
                  \node[blue] at (-0.9,-2.1) {C};
      
                  % Draw the mirror line x = 0
                  \draw[red,thick] (0,-4) -- (0,4) node[above right] {$x = 0$};
      
                  %Draw the perpendicular distance from M to the opposite side of the mirror
                  \draw[red,black] (-2,3) -- (2,3);
                  \draw[red,black] (-4,-0) -- (4,0);
                  \draw[red,black] (-1,-2) -- (1,-2);
      
                  % Calculate and draw the reflected triangle
                  \fill[green,opacity=0.3] (2,3) -- (4,0) -- (1,-2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[green,thick] (2,3) -- (4,0) -- (1,-2)-- cycle;
                  \node[green] at (2.2,3.3) {A'};
                  \node[green] at (4.3,0.2) {B'};
                  \node[green] at (1.5,-1.9) {C'};
                \end{tikzpicture}
              </latex-image>
            </image>
      
          </activity>
          <p>
            <term>Key Takeaway</term>
          </p>
          <p>
            We can derive coordinate rules from reflection. The coordinate rules for reflection depend
             on the axis or line being used. Letâ€™s derive the rules under the reflection across the y-axis:
          </p>
          <p>
            Consider the coordinates of the triangle <m>ABC</m> and its reflected image <m>A'B'C'</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <m>A(-2,3) \to A'(2,3)</m> 
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <m>B(-4,0) \to B'(4,0)</m> 
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <m>C(-1,-2) \to C'(1,-2) </m> 
                </p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </p>
          <p>
            The y-coordinates remains the same, but the x-coordinate is negated. 
            Reflecting across the y-axis means the point moves horizontally to the opposite side.
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore, the coordinate rule under the reflection across the y-axis is: <term><m>(x,y) \to (x,-y)</m></term>
          </p>
        
    </subsubsection>

    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-reflection-on-the-line-y-equals-x">
        <title>Reflection on the Line y = x</title>
        <example>
            <statement>
              <p>
                Draw the image of the pentagon under the reflection on the  line <m>y = x.</m>
              </p>
      
              <image>
              <latex-image label="object_mirror_line_example">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                  % Draw the grid lines
                  \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                  % Draw x and y axes
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};

                  % Grid and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1); % Tick marks on x-axis
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }
    
                    \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y); % Tick marks on y-axis
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }
      
                  % Draw the original pentagon
                  \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (-1,0) -- (-3,0) -- (-4,2) -- (-2,3.5) -- (0,2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[blue,thick] (-1,0) -- (-3,0) -- (-4,2) -- (-2,3.5) -- (0,2) -- cycle;
                  \node[right,blue] at (-1.2,0) {A};
                  \node[blue] at (-3.2,0) {B};
                  \node[blue] at (-4.2,2) {C};
                  \node[above,blue] at (-1.8,3.5) {D};
                  \node[blue] at (0.2,2) {E};
      
                  % Draw the mirror line x = y
                  \draw[red,thick] (-4,-4) -- (4,4) node[above right] {$y =x$};
                \end{tikzpicture}
              </latex-image>
            </image>
            </statement>
      
            <solution>
              <p>
                To obtain the image <m>A'</m> of <m>A</m> draw a perpendicular line from <m>A</m>the line <m>y = x</m> extend the 
                line the same distance on the opposite side of the line of reflection and mark the point as <m>A'.</m> Similarly, obtain the images 
                <m>B', C', D', E'</m> the images of vertices <m>B, C, D, E</m> respectively.
              </p>
              <p>
                Connect the images of the vertices to form the reflection of the pentagon. 
              </p> 
      
              <image>
              <latex-image label="object_mirror_line_example_solution">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                  % Draw the grid lines
                  \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                  % Draw x and y axes
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                \draw[thick,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};

                  % Grid and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1); % Tick marks on x-axis
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }
    
                    \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y); % Tick marks on y-axis
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }
      
                  % Draw the original pentagon
                  \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (-1,0) -- (-3,0) -- (-4,2) -- (-2,3.5) -- (0,2) -- cycle;
                  \draw[blue,thick] (-1,0) -- (-3,0) -- (-4,2) -- (-2,3.5) -- (0,2) -- cycle;
                  \node[right,blue] at (-1.2,0) {A};
                  \node[blue] at (-3.2,0) {B};
                  \node[blue] at (-4.2,2) {C};
                  \node[above,blue] at (-1.8,3.5) {D};
                  \node[blue] at (0.2,2) {E};
      
                  % Draw the mirror line x = y
                  \draw[red,thick] (-4,-4) -- (4,4) node[above right] {$y = x$};
      
                  %Draw the perpendicular distance from vertices to the opposite side of the mirror
                  \draw[black] (-1,0) -- (0,-1);
                  \draw[black] (-3,0) -- (0,-3);
                  \draw[black] (-4,2) -- (2,-4);
                  \draw[black] (-2,3.5) -- (3.5,-2);
                  \draw[black] (0,2) -- (2,0);
      
                  % Draw the image of the pentagon
                  \fill[purple,opacity=0.3] (0,-1) -- (0,-3) -- (2,-4) -- (3.5,-2) -- (2,0) -- cycle;
                  \draw[purple,thick] (0,-1) -- (0,-3) -- (2,-4) -- (3.5,-2) -- (2,0) -- cycle;
                  \node[left,purple] at (0,-1.2) {A'};
                  \node[purple] at (0,-3.2) {B'};
                  \node[purple] at (2,-4.2) {C'};
                  \node[right,purple] at (3.5,-2.2) {D'};
                  \node[purple] at (2.2,0) {E'};
                \end{tikzpicture}
              </latex-image>
            </image>
            </solution>
          </example>
        
      </subsubsection>
      <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-reflection-on-the-line-y-equals-negative-x">
        <title>Reflection on the Line y = -x</title>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Draw the image of the following object under a reflection in the line <m>y = -x.</m>
                </p>
                <image>
                    <latex-image label="Object_image_example_quiz">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % Draw the grid lines
                        \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);
            
                        % Draw the axes
                        \draw[thin,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[right] {x-axis};
                        \foreach \x in {-4,...,4}{
                        \draw(\x,.25)--(\x,-.25) node[below]{\x};
                         }
            
                        \draw[thin,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[above] {y-axis}; 
                        \foreach \y/\ytext in {-4/-4,-3/-3,-2/-2,-1/-1,0/0,1/1, 2/2, 3/3, 4/4}
                        \draw[shift={(0,\y)}] (2pt,0pt) -- (-2pt,0pt) node[left] {$\ytext$};
            
            
                        % Draw the original object
                        \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (2,5) -- (2,3) -- (4,2) -- (0,0) --cycle;
                        \draw[blue,thick] (2,5) -- (2,3) -- (4,2) -- (0,0) -- cycle;
                        \node[blue] at (2.2,5.2) {A};
                        \node[blue] at (2.2,3) {B};
                        \node[blue] at (4.2,2) {C};
                        \node[left,blue] at (.1,.2) {D};
                        
                        % Draw the mirror line x = y
                          \draw[red,thick] (-4,4) -- (4,-4) node[above right] {$y = -x$};
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                   The image of the figure under the reflection on the line <m>y = -x</m> is: 
                </p>
                <image>
                    <shortdescription>Line of reflection</shortdescription>
                    <latex-image label="Object_image_example_solution">
                      \begin{tikzpicture}
                        
                        % Draw the grid lines
                        \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);
            
                        % Draw the axes
                        \draw[thin,-&gt;] (-5,0) -- (5,0) node[right] {x-axis};
                        \foreach \x in {-4,...,4}{
                        \draw(\x,.25)--(\x,-.25) node[below]{\x};
                         }
            
                        \draw[thin,-&gt;] (0,-5) -- (0,5) node[above] {y-axis}; 
                        \foreach \y/\ytext in {-4/-4,-3/-3,-2/-2,-1/-1,0/0,1/1, 2/2, 3/3, 4/4}
                        \draw[shift={(0,\y)}] (2pt,0pt) -- (-2pt,0pt) node[left] {$\ytext$};
            
            
                        % Draw the original object
                        \fill[blue,opacity=0.3] (2,5) -- (2,3) -- (4,2) -- (0,0) --cycle;
                        \draw[blue,thick] (2,5) -- (2,3) -- (4,2) -- (0,0) -- cycle;
                        \node[blue] at (2.2,5.2) {A};
                        \node[blue] at (2.2,3) {B};
                        \node[blue] at (4.2,2) {C};
                        \node[left,blue] at (.1,.2) {D};
                        
                        % Draw the mirror line x = y
                          \draw[red,thick] (-4,4) -- (4,-4) node[above right] {$y = -x$};
            
                        % Calculate and draw the image
                        \fill[red,opacity=0.3](-5,-2) -- (-3,-2) -- (-2,-4) -- (0,0) -- cycle;
                        \draw[red,thick] (-5,-2) -- (-3,-2) -- (-2,-4) -- (0,0) -- cycle;
                        \node[red] at (-5.2,-2) {A'};
                        \node[below,red] at (-3.2,-2) {B'};
                        \node[red] at (-2.2,-4){C'};
                        \node[right,red] at (-.1,-.1) {D'};
                        
                      \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                  </image>
            </solution>
        </example>
        
      </subsubsection>
